<br>
what i mean by this, is that you, much like me, and a lot of my friends, do not WANT sympathy.. it's understandable.. i have been like that before.. but instead of asking for sympathy, ask for someone just to listen to you... go out to a bar, have a few drinks, do something you really enjoy.. talk to one of your friends over a beer or something like that.. i know people who do it all the time, and it works them wonders. <p>yep. i don't have a signature yet... but i assure you, when i do, it will be original, tasteful, ironic, perplexing, laughable, interesting, 'cool', eye-catching, droll, and otherwise funny. </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#242422><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub12.ezboard.com/ugarbhad.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Garbhad</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/misc_2.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1910<br> <font color=#DDA0DD>(8/1/01 10:50:06 pm)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.personal.engin.umich.edu/~rhanold/swedchef/chef7.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I wish I were dead for real </span><hr size=1> I am an avid listener of the radio show Love Line. Adam Carolla is the man. Now anyway, many a times do i hear callers call up with similar situations. This is basically what they tell them.<br>
<br>
You are better to find out now than in two or three years down the road after you have already had children, bought a house, new car etc..<br>
<br>
A person like her, probably has her own demons that she is dealing with, whether it be from an experience earlier in her childhood ormore recent. The only thing you can do is to work up the courage to continue on day by day. <br>
<br>
I went through something like this back in 95. I had been with my girlfriend at the time for 2 years. We had planned on getting married and had everything arranged. Well I went to the field for 3 weeks on a training excercise. I come back and found that she had fallen for some gas station attendant(who i later found out was being followed by the police for his involvements in a local drug ring). I tried salvaging everything as best as I could. I talked her in to sharing the rent at the apartment until the lease was up and I could move back on base. She was there not more than 2 weeks when she invited the asshole in to the place to share her part of the rent. Well that went over like a lead balloon. Next thing I know, i have police surveilance vehicles outside my house and am being followed to the base everyday.<br>
<br>
I had enough and moved out and stuck her with the rent and got my name taken off the lease. Last I heard they were both serving time in Colorado state pen. <br>
<br>
Anyway, my point is, you will make i through man, no one that does something like that to another human, is worth your own life. There is so much more for you at your age to get out and see/do. Think about all the places you haven't been, and perhaps set up a trip, take time away from your current surroundings and let it all fade away behind you.<br>
<br>
Good luck to you man, I hope everything works out for you in the end. <p>~Garbhad Brainbender~
